    <h2>About</h2>

    <h3>The Opquast Project</h3>

    <p><a href="http://www.opquast.com">Opquast</a> (Open Quality Standards) is an ecosystem aimed
    at improvement and rentability of websites.</p>

    <ul>
      <li>Checklists to understand and produce (<a
        href="http://checklists.opquast.com/fr/opquast-website">Opquast Website</a>, <a
        href="http://checklists.opquast.com/fr/opquastv2">Qualité Web</a>, <a
        href="http://checklists.opquast.com/fr/seo">SEO</a>, <a
        href="http://checklists.opquast.com/fr/opendata">Open data</a> checklists…)</li>
      <li>Testing tools to drive website quality
      (Opquast Desktop, <a href="http://reporting.opquast.com">Opquast reporting</a>)</li>
      <li>Professionnals to help you with your web projects
      (<a href="http://partners.opquast.com/">partners.opquast.com</a>)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Opquast Desktop</h3>

    <p>Opquast Desktop is an application that allows you to analyze your website using different
    quality or accessibility checklists.</p>

    <h2>Analyze a page</h2>

    <h3>Quick analysis</h3>

    <ul>
      <li>Press the toolbar button <img src="img/button.png" alt="Button screenshot" />
      to open the Opquast Desktop panel. This button can also be used to close the panel;</li>

      <li>If the current URI has already been analyzed, the application will show last analysis
      results;</li>

      <li>Otherwise, you will be offered to launch the analysis on the current page;</li>

      <li>To launch or relaunch, click on the appropriate button;</li>

      <li>The results will be directly visible on the panel;</li>

      <li>You can launch or relaunch the analysis at any time.</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>Note:</strong> You can also use "Opquast Desktop" menu in
    "Tools > Web developer" or the keyboard shortcut "ctrl + alt + o".</p>

    <h3>Result management</h3>

    <ul>
      <li>Search: type in the search box and results will be automatically filtered using your
      query.</li>

      <li>Filters: you can show results issued from only one of the available checklists or with a
      given status. Use the select boxes available in the result header row.</li>

      <li>Details: You can view a given result details by clicking on any line. For each test,
      Opquast Desktop provides you with a global comment and, when it’s relevant, a list of involved
      DOM nodes. The details window can be closed at any time by using the ESC key. You can show the
      previous or the next detail window using the appropriate links or the arrow keys of your
      keyboard.</li>

      <li>Export: the export button allows you to export your analysis  results to a CSV file or to
      Opquast Reporting.</li>
    </ul>

